In [[algebraic geometry]], a '''derived stack''' is, roughly, a [[stack (mathematics)|stack]] together with a [[sheaf of spectra|sheaf of commutative ring spectra]].<ref>{{harvnb|Mathew|Meier|2013|loc=Definition 2.6.}}</ref> It generalizes a [[derived scheme]]. Derived stacks are the "spaces" studied in [[derived algebraic geometry]].<ref name=Vezzosi2011>{{cite journal|last=Vezzosi|first=Gabriele|title=What is ... a Derived Stack?|journal=Notices of the AMS|date=August 2011|volume=58|issue=7|pages=955–958|url=http://www.ams.org/notices/201107/rtx110700955p.pdf|accessdate=4 March 2014}}</ref>

